  "Inertia is the natural tendency of an object to resist changes in its state of motion. An object at rest tends to stay at rest, and an object in motion tends to keep moving at the same speed and direction. Mass is the measure of inertia.": "",
  "What does the term 'constant velocity' mean?": "",
