  "The object moves with unchanging speed in an unchanging direction": "",
  "The object is speeding up at a steady rate each second": "",
  "The object is slowing down but maintaining the same direction": "",
  "Constant velocity means both the speed and the direction of motion remain the same. If either speed or direction changes, the velocity is not constant. An object with constant velocity has zero acceleration.": "",
  "What is the meaning of 'net external force'?": "",
