  "Any single force that is applied internally within an object": "",
  "The force of gravity acting on an object near the surface": "",
  "The maximum amount of friction between two surfaces": "",
  "The net external force is the vector sum of all forces acting on an object from outside sources. If external forces balance out, the net external force is zero and the object's motion does not change.": "",
  "What does 'dynamic equilibrium' mean?": "",
  "An object is at rest with no forces acting on it at all": "",
  "An object is accelerating due to an unbalanced net force": "",
  "An object moves at constant velocity with zero net force": "",
  "An object is vibrating rapidly while staying in one place": "",
  "Dynamic equilibrium describes a moving object with zero net force. The object moves at constant velocity — it does not speed up, slow down, or change direction. This contrasts with static equilibrium, where the object is at rest with zero net force.": "",
