  "The physical state of matter such as solid, liquid, or gas": "",
  "The amount of energy an object has stored inside of it": "",
  "An object's state of motion describes whether it is at rest or in motion, and if moving, its speed and direction (velocity). Newton's First Law says an object's state of motion does not change unless a net force acts on it.": "",
  "What is meant by the phrase 'an object in motion stays in motion'?": "",
